# Client-side
<client>
<server>
smtp
</server>
 <name>
SMTP multipart using mime API
 </name>
<stdin>
From: different
To: another

body
</stdin>
 <command>
smtp://%HOSTIP:%SMTPPORT/646 --mail-rcpt recipient@example.com --mail-from sender@example.com -F "=(;type=multipart/alternative" -F "= <body>This is the html version</body>;type=text/html" -F "=This is the plain text version" -F "=)" -F "=@log/test646.txt" -H "From: different" -H "To: another" -H "Reply-To: <followup@example.com>"
</command>
<file name="log/test646.txt">
This is an attached file.

It may contain any type of data.
</file>
</client>

